\n<li>Added ability to change task status and lead status directly from the table.<\/li>\n<li>Added ability to save last order for specific tables.<\/li>\n<li>Copy project feature now will copy custom fields too.<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Redesigned proposal view.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>New HTML view for a contract.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Added contract comments.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>New email template for contract expiration sent to staff members.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Improvements in proposal and contract editor, change the theme to inlite.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Improvements in Stripe payment processing.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Option to show in calendar tasks only to assigned to the logged in staff.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>CSRF protection by default will be enabled.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>In admin area knowledge base default will be list view instead of kanban.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Improvements in tables.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>When a ticket is opened by contact, in tickets table list customer will be shown as the contact first name and last name instead of the company name.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Updated Codeigniter to 3.1.8.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Performance and design improvements.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Security Improvements.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Moved customer contacts view in a separate tab.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Removed Recurring ends on field for recurring tasks, invoices, expenses, replaced with Cycles.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Removed project billing type from projects table.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Removed storing the ticket IP\u00a0address.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Removed Bitcoin support for Stripe (Stripe is no longer supporting Bitcoin)<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed contract due date issue when renewing a contract.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed tickets table custom fields column order not correct on customers area.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed issue in top search for regular staff members.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed web to lead form builder not working properly on Edge browser.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed period selector\u00a0&#8220;Last month&#8221; on reports not correct.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed some forms not working properly on Safari latest update.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed TinyMCE editor add new lines upon saving on Surveys area.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed lead monthly report not working properly.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div>Fixed shipping street merge field not showing on invoices\/estimates\/credit notes.<\/div>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<hr \/>\n<h4 id=\"upgrading_notes\">Upgrading to version 2.0<\/h4>\n<hr \/>\n<h4><strong>Create backup<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Before upgrading to version 2.0 it&#8217;s strongly recommended to create database and files backup.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h4><strong> Ends on date field for recurring options<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Note that if you don&#8217;t have any recurring data, you can ignore this note.<\/p>\n<p>In previous versions when you create eq recurring invoice, task or expense there is a field <strong>Recurring ends on<\/strong> and this field is a date field.<\/p>\n<p>The <strong>recurring ends on <\/strong>field is<strong> removed<\/strong> in version 2.0 and <strong>no longer will be used<\/strong>, this field is replaced with total\u00a0<strong>Cycles<\/strong> field.<\/p>\n<p>Because the update script is unable to process this field <strong>before update<\/strong> if you have added Recurring ends on date\u00a0field on any recurring invoices, tasks, expenses, you will need to write somewhere the end date for the specific invoice, task, expense, <strong>then after the update you can decide if you want to mark this not recurring\u00a0 invoice, task or expense or adjust the cycles to fit <\/strong><strong>your needs.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You can use the table filter to find any recurring invoices, tasks, expenses.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>To find recurring invoices on the menu click Invoices and on the right side filter button select All first to deselect all filters then select Recurring invoices<\/li>\n<li>To find recurring expenses, on the menu click Expenses and on the right side filter button select All first to deselect all filters then select Recurring<\/li>\n<li>To find recurring tasks, on the menu click Tasks and on the right side filter button select All first to deselect all filters then select Recurring<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>It&#8217;s important to re-check all the recurring data with Recurring ends on fields in case they are ended immediately after successfully update to prevent the cron job re-creating the eq. invoices again. If you have a lot recurring data that you must check, the best is to disable the cron job temporary and then after you re-check this, configure the cron job again<\/strong><\/span>.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h4><strong>Removed Bitcoin support for Stripe<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>If in <strong>Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;Payment Gateways-&gt;Stripe Checkout, <\/strong>if\u00a0you configured Bitcoin support for Stripe, then this option will be no longer available, in case you are using Bitcoin for payments you should have in mind that your customers will be no longer able to pay you via Bitcoin and Stripe.<\/p>\n<p>More info about this can be found on Stripe official blog <a href=\"https:\/\/stripe.com\/blog\/ending-bitcoin-support\">post<\/a>.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h4><strong> A note for using your own files or your own theme for customers area<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Perfex CRM version 2.0 comes with huge changes in some functionalities and code including CSS styling.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you are using your <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/customers-templates\/\">own theme for customers<\/a> area, you may want to adjust the theme to be compatible with Perfex CRM version 2.0 or simply switch to the original Perfex CRM theme for customers in <strong>Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;Customers<\/strong>.<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If you are using <a style=\"color: #ff0000;\" href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/edit-view-files-without-messing-the-core-view-files\/\">my_ prefixed files<\/a> for any feature, <strong>it&#8217;s highly recommended to re-check the files<\/strong> and compare it with the original files in case you getting some errors and tables are not loading.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<hr \/>\n<h4>Using Amazon AWS for sending emails?<\/h4>\n<p>If before the update you were using Amazon AWS for sending emails after you successfully upgraded, please navigate to <strong>Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;Email<\/strong> and set\u00a0<strong>Mail Engine<\/strong> to <strong>PHPMailer<\/strong><\/p>\n<h4><strong>Customers area knowledge base links<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Customers are knowledge base is improved,\u00a0note that this is only affecting customers area (internal staff articles are not changed), also if you are not using knowledge base you can ignore this.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Article links:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>The links in versions before 2.0 were:<\/p>\n<p>yourcrminstallation.com\/knowledge-base\/[slug]<\/p>\n<p>In version 2.0 are changed to:<\/p>\n<p>yourcrminstallation.com\/knowledge-base\/article\/[slug]<\/p>\n<p><strong>Group links<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>The links in versions before 2.0 were:<\/p>\n<p>yourcrminstallation.com\/knowledge-base?groupid=[group-id]<\/p>\n<p>In version 2.0 are changed to:<\/p>\n<p>yourcrminstallation.com\/knowledge-base\/category\/[group-slug]<\/p>\n<p><strong>In case you are referencing knowledge base links on other websites or directly in the article content<\/strong> (via the editor), the best is to re-check the links and change them manually, we have included a backward compatibility for this but probably in future updates, the backward compatibility will be removed.<\/p>\n<h4><strong>Clear your browser\/Cloudflare cache<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>After the update, <strong>it&#8217;s highly recommended to clear your browser and Cloudflare (if using) cache<\/strong> in case you are experiencing some issue with CSS or Javascript.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h4><strong>Having problems?<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>We are always striving to help our customers in case you are experiencing some issues with Perfex CRM, in case you are experiencing some issue don&#8217;t hesitate to <a href=\"https:\/\/my.perfexcrm.com\">open support ticket<\/a> or if you want to report a possible bug and your support is expired, you can contact us at info@perfexcrm.com we will be happy to take a look.<\/p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to include enough information in your ticket\/email so we can faster identify the issue, additionally, you may\u00a0want to turn debug mode as explained <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/faq\/how-to-set-debug-mode\/\">here<\/a> to get any error messages outputted.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>You may want to check the upgrading notes below Changelog: Added new feature subscriptions via Stripe. Added feature to track specific emails if they are opened. Ability to E-Sign contracts, estimates, proposals. Added period filters for expenses detailed report. Added email notifications option for tickets, per contact. Added file upload for task comments. Added option [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[23],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-3545","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-changelog"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3545","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embedd